The Midgaard postmaster has received transit-hazard filings from convoys attempting the Three Spines approach to the Cinder Gate, and the route cannot be certified for the next season without updated threat data. Ash scorpion reavers have expanded into the First Spine ingress zone, toll hijacker captains have seized the Third Spine checkpoint, and broker intimidators are blocking the Cinder Gate queue approach. Eliminate one of each and file an engagement report so the postmaster can update the route's hazard advisory.
The Three Spines survey data has been filed with the Midgaard postmaster's transit certification office. Scorpion presence on the ingress zone, hijacker activity at the Third Spine checkpoint, and intimidator operations at the gate approach are all now documented. The postmaster has issued updated crossing advisories to all bonded convoy operators registered for the next authorization cycle.

